The paper deals with the communication requirements of distributed computations, which is a central topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The problems studied in the paper, such as matrix multiplication, sorting, and FFT, are fundamental problems in computer science and are often studied in the context of distributed computing. Therefore, the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.SC (scientific computing), and cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). However, since the focus of the paper is on communication complexity, we rank cs.DC as the most likely category, followed by the other categories in decreasing order of relevance.
